----------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party techniques and libraries (ported or documented, not vendored)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The image-to-ascii skill ports circle-geometry and contrast math from
ascii-img-react (https://github.com/mrmartineau/ascii-img-react, MIT) and
follows Alex Harri's "ASCII characters are not pixels" technique.

Skills under skills/ document third-party frameworks and libraries
(Textual, Bubble Tea, Ratatui, ascii-img-react, textmode.js). Each retains
its own upstream license, held by its respective authors.
